1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) - The paper deals with point set registration, which is a common problem in computer vision. 
2. cs.GR (Graphics) - Point set registration is also a common problem in computer graphics, and the paper proposes a method that can be applied to various shapes, including human body shapes, hands, and faces. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The proposed method uses a Gaussian mixture model and a statistical shape model, which are both machine learning techniques. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with shape modeling and registration, which are relevant topics in multimedia applications such as 3D modeling and animation. 
5. cs.RO (Robotics) - Point set registration is also a relevant problem in robotics, and the proposed method can be useful for robot perception and manipulation tasks.
